UP elections: Chief minister Akhilesh Yadav resigns 
11-3-2017 
Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Akhilesh Yadav today tendered his resignation to Governor Ram Naik after his Samjawadi Partyâ€™s massive defeat in Assembly polls. The Governor has accepted his resignation and has asked him to continue till further arrangements, a Raj Bhawan spokesman said.

Soon after accepting defeat at a hurriedly convened press conference, Akhilesh proceeded to Raj Bhawan to put in his papers.

Read more

Earlier while addressing media, he had stated that he will review the performance of his party booth-wise to find out the reasons of defeat and stressed that perhaps the people voted for more development. 
